Answer for Problem #3
The tradeoff relationship between price and demand- The management dilemmma is that the relationship between price and demand must be carefully analyzed in order for the two to  compliment eachother. The price must be set in a way that it maximimizes demand, while still creating enough of a profit to cover expenses and make money. A break even model can be used to see what price is absolutely neccessary to cover expenses and then raising the price slightly over that to make a profit.



Answer for Problem #4
A logical upper limit was used in the Great Threads Model. Only a certain number of items can be created when you have so many employees. The number of employees is an example of a "logical upper limit". The concept of a logical upper limit is that it is  a constraint within a problem that defines the upper bounds that can be reached before a problem is illoogical.
